SIMPLE: floral
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Floral
<hw>Flo"ral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Floralis</ets> belonging to <ets>Flora</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>floral</ets>. See <er>Flora</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pertaining to Flora, or to flowers; made of flowers; <as>as,
<ex>floral</ex> games, wreaths</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Containing, or belonging to, a
flower; <as>as, a <ex>floral</ex> bud; a <ex>floral</ex> leaf;
<ex>floral</ex> characters.</as></def> <rj><au>Martyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Floral envelope</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>the
calyx and corolla, one or the other of which (mostly the corolla) may be
wanting.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Florally</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Floral
<hw>Flo`r⟦eacute⟧al"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>flor⟦eacute⟧al</ets>, fr. L. <ets>flos</ets>, <ets>floris</ets>,
flower.]</ety> <def>The eight month of the French republican calendar.
It began April 20, and ended May 19. See
<er>Vend⟦eacute⟧miare</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Floren</ent>⟦br⟧
